        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3718756039" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12416949694363752490">What a book. What an amazing book. <br/><br/>I had always thought the key dystopian novels were Fahrenheit 451, 1984 and Brave New World, but add this one to the list. In my mind this trumps them all, even Fahrenheit, which has always been my favourite. <br/><br/>This book is incredible. Much like East of Eden, I believe everything there is to know about humanity is in this. <br/><br/>Walter Tevis has achieved perfection for me twice so far - first with The Queen’s Gambit, and now with Mockingbird. <br/><br/>I urge everybody to read i</span>
  <span id="freeText12416949694363752490" style="display:none">What a book. What an amazing book. <br /><br />I had always thought the key dystopian novels were Fahrenheit 451, 1984 and Brave New World, but add this one to the list. In my mind this trumps them all, even Fahrenheit, which has always been my favourite. <br /><br />This book is incredible. Much like East of Eden, I believe everything there is to know about humanity is in this. <br /><br />Walter Tevis has achieved perfection for me twice so far - first with The Queen’s Gambit, and now with Mockingbird. <br /><br />I urge everybody to read it. It’s that good.</span>
