<span id="freeTextContainer9604516091945112121">A rare 5 Stars from me; completely subjective of course, but I absolutely loved <b>Mockingbird</b>. Sometimes a book just hits all the right buttons at the right time. It doesn’t mean it’s the greatest book ever written. But for me, it was the perfect book at the perfect time. Tevis has written a very human story. It’s also a very moving and uplifting story.<br/><br/>[...]<br/><br/><b>Mockingbird</b> is a book that made me fall in love with reading again. As two of the main characters rediscover the joy of reading, I was inspire</span>
  <span id="freeText9604516091945112121" style="display:none">A rare 5 Stars from me; completely subjective of course, but I absolutely loved <b>Mockingbird</b>. Sometimes a book just hits all the right buttons at the right time. It doesn’t mean it’s the greatest book ever written. But for me, it was the perfect book at the perfect time. Tevis has written a very human story. It’s also a very moving and uplifting story.<br /><br />[...]<br /><br /><b>Mockingbird</b> is a book that made me fall in love with reading again. As two of the main characters rediscover the joy of reading, I was inspired to seek out some of the stories and poems referenced in the narrative. I have always enjoyed reading but this book made me appreciate how important it is to me. Imagine a world where nobody reads anymore. If you ever feel like you have lost your enthusiasm for reading, please read this book.<br /><br />My full review is here on my blog: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://biginjapangrayman.wordpress.com/2021/01/17/mockingbird-1980-by-walter-tevis/">https://biginjapangrayman.wordpress.c...</a></span>
